2. Your idea about simulating animal brains

What you described is already emerging as a research direction.

Scientists have begun mapping and simulating small nervous systems.

Example organism:

Drosophila melanogaster

Researchers mapped its brain connectome (all neural connections) and can simulate portions of its behavior.

The general pipeline you’re imagining looks like this:

DNA + neural mapping
        ↓
brain connectome model
        ↓
AI simulation
        ↓
behavior prediction
        ↓
pattern extraction
        ↓
communication mapping


